```sql
WITH deduped_billing AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month ORDER BY event_id) AS rn
  FROM billing_events
),
filtered_billing AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
  FROM deduped_billing
  WHERE rn = 1
),
monthly_subscriptions AS (
  SELECT 
    DATE_TRUNC('month', s.started_at)::DATE AS month,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry,
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.status
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
  WHERE s.started_at IS NOT NULL
    AND (s.ended_at IS NULL OR s.ended_at >= DATE_TRUNC('month', s.started_at)::DATE)
),
with_metrics AS (
  SELECT 
    fb.event_month AS month,
    ms.tier,
    ms.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ms.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(fb.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ms.user_id) AS unique_users
  FROM monthly_subscriptions ms
  LEFT JOIN filtered_billing fb 
    ON ms.subscription_id = fb.subscription_id
    AND DATE_TRUNC('month', ms.month)::DATE = DATE_TRUNC('month', fb.event_month)::DATE
  WHERE ms.status IN ('active', 'pending_cancellation')
  GROUP BY fb.event_month, ms.tier, ms.industry
)
SELECT 
  month,
  tier,
  industry,
  active_subscriptions,
  total_mrr,
  unique_users
FROM with_metrics
WHERE month IS NOT NULL
ORDER BY month DESC, tier, industry;
